{"title":"Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #14: Basso SV","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-basso-sv","date":1741965196000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-basso-sv\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #14: Basso SV</a></p>\n\n<p>Whether you’re looking for a new bike or just want to try out some of the world’s best, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">Cyclist Track Days</a> offer a unique experience to test the latest top-end bikes from the leading brands on the market. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Next up in our run-through of the incredible bikes that you can test ride at this years Track Days is the Basso SV.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The SV is Basso’s brand new all-round road race bike, replacing the Diamante SV aero bike. It’s more versatile than the Diamante but also lighter and just as aero.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Basso’s head of product and marketing Leonardo Basso said of the SV, ‘Because we don’t have a WorldTour team we don’t need to produce bikes for pro riders. Instead, we can create a bike that is for real world riders.’</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For staff writer Laurence Kilpatrick’s full review you’ll have to keep an eye out for the next issue of Cyclist – spoiler he calls it ‘an exciting step forward for Basso’ – but in the meantime check out <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/basso-sv-2025-review\">his first impressions</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Basso SV will be at the following Track Days events:</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>26<sup>th</sup> April 2025, Odd Down Cycle Track Bath,<br />17<sup>th</sup> May 2025, Lee Valley VeloPark London,<br />7<sup>th</sup> June 2025, The Brownlee Centre, Leeds</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For more information on Cyclist Track Days click <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-information\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://www.eventbrite.com/cc/cyclist-track-days-2025-3855053\" target=\"_blank\">BOOK YOUR TICKET HERE</a></strong></h3>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-scott-addict-rc\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #7: Scott Addict RC</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-trek-madone-slr\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #5: Trek Madone SLR</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cyclist-track-days-2025-bikes-van-rysel-rcr\">Cyclist Track Days 2025 bikes #1: Van Rysel RCR</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/basso-sv-2025-review\">Basso SV: First ride review on Basso’s featherweight aero racer</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/basso-sv-2025\">New Basso SV all-round road bike replaces aero Diamante SV</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n      